rComments: Really unorganized prof, u should've seen the discord chat. Posts the lectures 20 minutes before class expecting us to have listened to everything. Doesn't reply to our questions and gets made when we ask stuff about her vague instructions. Takes forever to do her labs simply because you just would'nt know what it was she was asking

This was a summer course and it really wasn't that bad. I actually enjoyed the content and the "group project" we were assigned (which you could also do individually) was pretty interesting. I'll admit her lectures aren't super content-heavy and her exams can be a little vague, but most of the course is "common sense" once you learn the basics.

Prof Hogan is very flexible and her exams clearly reflect what is posted in her lectures. Attendance is not mandatory but she gives hints at what to expect in her exams. Extra credit is given as an option for a grade boost so take advantage of that. Group projects can be done individually and is a way to boost your mark.

If there was a trophy for the worst professor of the year/existence it would be this one. Replies late, your better off teaching yourself. Secondly, we had a group project to do, and the instructions were so unclear it took us longer to understand what she wanted rather than doing the work itself. 
AVOID AT ALL COST, SAVE YOURSELVES!!!!!!

Her slides/material taught is simple but is not reflective of midterms and exams, which makes her intentions very unclear. Communication with students is extremely poor as she rarely responds to emails. Don't expect things to be finalized until the day of the exam.
she is extremely disorganized and very unclear regarding her intentions. Never follows the syllabus and is always late posting information and lectures. Questions on her exams make zero sense. AVOID

Gives the submission links for assignments after they are due on multiple occasions. Her lectures are very basic voice recordings over the slides, where she basically just reads the slide material. One of the previous classes I had her in, her exam was riddled with spelling and grammatical errors. STAY AWAY

This prof is the most disorganized one I've had. She isn't clear about due dates, doesn't follow deadlines, takes months to hand back assignments, and can be rude answering questions. She told us 30 mins before the midterm that we could use zoom instead of respondus. It's hard to know what she expects of you as she posts rubrics late. Easy A though

Long winded and boring explanations on slides with a lot of 6 min tangents not relevant to the course on all asynchronous slides. Very disorganized and boring. Ive also had friends in her other classes and she doesnt post submission links or groups on time and doesnt respond to emails. AVOID!!!

Depending on class she can be easy, avoid if possible. She is all over the place. Posts lectures with simple voice overs once a week, tests minimal textbook content so midterms are a guessing game even if you study the material. Instructions for projects are vague and you spend more time figuring out what she is asking than doing the project.

OK... idk why a lot of students dislike her, i mean yes she says things that can be misinterpreted or taken the wrong way, but as a prof she's actually not bad. Her tests are really fair and mostly common sense, she doesn't ask specific questions. For papers, she offers a lot of help on her live zoom sessions, and she's really flexible w/ due dates

PLEASE AVOID at all costs. Had her 3 semesters in a row (unwillingly) and is the worst prof ever. Easy class, but she is all over the place and will give you contradicting and extremely vague instructions. Also makes a lot of subtle racist remarks so beware. Don't know how she's still a prof as she's gotten many complaints. uOttawa do better.

She's all over the place lacks communication skills and is a boring lecturer. But her class is DEAD EASY she asks the most basic questions on her exam and is such an easy marker for the paper. She definitely cares that students do well.

She gives very vague explanations of assignments and assessments but then grades it very toughly. It's annoying when professors are vague about their expectations, but it's worse when they are vague and then grade on very specific things and expect you to read their mind. Says that she's a fair prof, but this is not true. Avoid her at all costs.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: The sad thing about this is that the course entails really interesting content concerning social roles in health care but instead it was taught by a women who made light of blm and talked to minority students in condescending ways. Assignments not clear, exam full of errors and missing answers, promises one thing does the exact opposite. AVOID!!!
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Participation matters', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: DO NOT take her classes. Worst prof I have ever encountered. Told us one thing about the final during the sem, but made it completely different than what she told us the day BEFORE the final. She sucks at communication, and won't email back until weeks later. Violated university rules by not giving us enough time during the final. Just don't do it.

At 4am the day of our exam she shortened the time limit (violating academic regulations) and did not respond to a single email seeking clarification or an explanation. This made for an extremely stressful lead up to the exam (full of grammar mistakes, weird online layout). Overall rude, disrespectful, unprofessional - would not recommend.
Do not take her classes.

She doesn't reply to any emails. Does not communicate with students efficiently and accurately. Grading criteria is messy and not accurate. She says one thing in class and then grades papers by doing something completely different. AVOID AVOID AVOID AT ALL COSTS. YOU BASICALLY HAVE TO TEACH THE COURSE TO YOURSELF. Save yourself and don't take her.

This prof was so bad. Would not give clear instructions for discussion posts even when we asked. Didn't grade discussion posts for months so we had no idea if we were doing them right. Her lectures were just personal stories, not helpful. Had to read the entire textbook. Exam had so many spelling mistakes & mostly textbook based questions.

in my opinion not emotionally stable enough to be teaching. she clearly can't handle another job outside of being an RN. takes months to mark simple discussion post, unorganized, never responds to emails, is rude to students. lack of communication - changed exam time limit the day of. needs some time away from teaching or maybe professional help

A literal nightmare. She does not know how to communicate with her students, and when she does it's often condescending and patronizing. Talks way more about her own experience than actual course content. Petty as hell. Do your best to avoid her.

Professor Hogan is one of the worst profs I have encountered! She does does not communicate with her students, very unorganized, grades unfairly and is extremely unclear about tests and assignments. She simply does not care about her students at all, and puts her other job above this one. Avoid her at all costs!!

She does not care about her students, she either takes weeks to respond to your emails or does not respond at all. She is an unfair grader who takes marks off for no apparent reason. Her lectures lack direction as she talks about her personal life more than the course content at times. Avoid this prof if you can.

Dr. Hogan takes weeks to respond to emails, months to return grades, her essay marking is unfairly tough, and marks are often docked for no reason. It's not a hard class, but the headache from this professor was way too much. On top of all this, she is disrespectful and rude to her students.

Not sure if it was because the class was online but I definitely did not enjoy it. Labs were super easy but her midterm and exam had questions that were not covered in the class. She does not teach the material well and purely reads off the powerpoint.

It amazes me how ignorant this professor is from not answering emails to ignoring questions asked in class. I do not know what she is like In person, but she made learning online very difficult and stressful. It is clear she does not care about her students at all. She also did not follow her own syllabus AT ALL which is very inconvenient.

She implied in her syllabus that she will post recordings which she never did and when I asked her about the recordings, she criticized me for her own mistake. This class was unbearable and quite difficult to follow. She also posted labs without any announcement so students were unaware there was a lab to do on bright space.

Her exams do not match what she teaches. The midterm and final was all over the place since students did not know what to expect. She does not really tell you if there will be questions from the textbook or the slides which makes it hard to study since the textbook contradicts her sides a lot of the times. Overall not the best professor.

Unprofessional, rude and condescending. She puts her other jobs above her teaching job. She is never prepared for teaching and she will leave you in the dark when it comes to expectations. She ignores emails if she wants to. She barely communicated with students and she taught lessons in her Live Q and A that was supposed to be for questions only.

I'll keep this short n simple. She seems like a pretty nice lady but she's not a great prof. This class is gonna be a grind with her since she kinda overcomplicates material and talks about her nursing career half the time. COURSE SPLIT: 2 sets of quizzes (15 each) Midterm + Final (15 each) 2 Papers (15 each) Peer review & a certificate (5 each)

Kerry-Anne makes learning online so difficult when she fails to cover important lecture content yet still includes it on the tests, meaning we need to learn it ourselves. Most of the time this happens because she goes off on a tangent talking about her personal nursing career for 90% of the slide. Quite rude and condescending in person and online.

I wish I had the chance to take one of her classes in person - I would love to know how her online school persona translates to real life. She isn't a good prof. Clearly doesn't care about the class or the students, and posts years-old slides with irrelevant and confusing information. Cares more about her nursing job and her personal life.
By far the worst prof I've ever had at uOttawa. Very inconsiderate towards students and inconsistent with expectations. Puts her 'regular nursing job' above her teaching position.

Med/Surg. She is never really prepares for lectures. It seems as though she just comes and says what comes to mind at that moment Her lack of organization made this class unbearable :( Slides were also really unorganized and not engaging at all.

KA doesn't really teach the material for this course in an efficient manner, and her expectations do not match when you compare what we are taught and what our exam questions / project requirements are. Super unclear so be ready to just pass on a wing and a prayer.

In my experience, this professor is rude and unprofessional. I had a lot of respect for her at first but she has quickly dropped to one of my least favorite professors I've ever had. Besides personal reasons... test questions are subjective, and she doesn't post the lecture till 24h before the quiz is due, so clear your schedule to cram study
Very rude to students, and does not like to help you learn. 10/10 DO NOT recommend. Very condescending. Basically teaching yourself the content.

Kerry-Anne is extremely unprofessional, disorganized, and confused by basic principles, "wait, do I have that right?" (KAH, 2019) She will manipulate stats to explain why she has a terrible rate-my-prof score -- this was explained in her first lecture. Way to admit you're terrible. "Oh, it's all the outliers." (KAH, 2019) Avoid if possible.

Overall, not a bad prof as she makes her requirements incredibly clear. However, she spends a lot of time defending her reputation to the class and when she's upset it shows in her quality of teaching. Has the capacity to be a great prof, she gives practice midterms and takes them up but she needs to regulate her emotions.

Hogan is amazing. As a nurse herself, she has a lot of stories to share and is very knowledgeable of the course content. You have to show up to her lectures because she doesn't upload all of her slides. She also gives exam hints in class. Easy A class if you attend class and study the slides. No textbook. She also plays JFL-gags every class.

If you're lazy you won't like her- she'll call you out. But, I didn't do any of the readings and studied very little and still got an A- because her lectures are so clear you could repeat them in your sleep. SHOW UP -she will set you up for success. No surprises on the exams and the labs are easy, make sure to take notes on how to do things on SPSS

Horrible! Never take stats! You basically do not learn anything in class and it is all over the place. Midterm was ok but the final was so bad. Did not expose us to the types of questions, it was just horrible and long. Do not take this will ruin your GPA.
Exams rarely test you on what is taught in class or in textbook (doesn't cover material you are tested on)
Great class, lectures were never the full 3 hours which is nice and her midterms/exams were pretty fair

I absolutely loved her class. She's so passionate about what she teaches, so her lectures were very interesting. She really cares about her students and enjoys sharing nursing stories and advice. Midterms and exams were very fair and easy, sometimes she will give some questions that are on the exams. Overall an easy class!
She was my best prof this semester, she wants you to do well and gives good exam hints, cares about her students, and gives good examples especially for nursing students.

Kerry-Anne made it worth it to wake up at 5:30 for my 8am. As a nurse herself, she is incredibly inspiring and you can tell that she loves her job. Wasn't a difficult class, as long as you show up and listen because she gives great midterm/exam hints, although some test questions are hard because they seem like they could be several answers.

Hogan was amazing! She really cares for her students and LOVES the nurses. Her slides in lectures are informative and she gives hints as to whats going to be on midterms/finals so, as long as you go to class it should be an easy A. I would definitely take one of her classes again, really great prof:)

makes lectures really interesting, gives hints for what's gonna be on exams! go to class because she gives good examples of situations that happen as a nurse and help you remember concepts better. no textbook and she plays funny videos in class!! love her

Love her! My favourite prof, she's super chill and funny! Makes going to class enjoyable. She tells you what she's putting on the midterms. Lectures are always shorter than what is scheduled (which I don't mind). You do need to show up to class though, she gives out her slides but a less detailed version and you'll miss out on good explanations

gives great lectures. she does read off her slides but then goes onto elaborate and give very interesting examples to further your understanding (all examples could be on exams so good to go to class). I would say the textbook isn't mandatory but I definitely would've done better had I used it. occasionally plays funny videos at the end of lectures

She's a really disorganized lecturer and most of the time the entire class was confused. She only kept us for around 40 minutes each week for a class that was supposed to be 2.5 hours. Rude to students and very condescending. She did make the class easier than other profs but you basically have to teach everything to yourself.

She is a decent lecturer but and the material was really easy, however her questions on midterms and final were very subjective. Nice lady but final was littered with content not covered in class. Not very fair in that regard.

Best Instructor To Class Health, she was horrible, very rude, condescending, pompous. Glad its over. Also, she makes a lot of jokes that are sad. If you don't have to take this course then don't, she doesn't care about her students. Sad.

The two midterms were very straight forward however the final had a lot of content which was not covered in class and very subjective. I really enjoyed the class however I felt that the final really did not represent the content taught. Mostly reads off the slides and hard to get a hold of outside of the classroom.

Says you'll need the textbook but it really isn't necessary (she's a co-author which is why she loves the book). Mostly reads off the slides, so don't worry too much if you miss a lecture. Exams are pretty easy but she does have questions about random small facts. LOVES to talk about her daughter as if she's the most amazing nurse ever.

Her exam questions were so subjective. "T/F, nursing today is a women's profession, T/F: a pandemic could happen today" and double negatives all over the MCQs. She also interrupted our midterm to tell a story about her daughter sneezing. Hard to reach by email. I recommend avoiding her.

She is super obsessed with herself and although she is a good lecturer, she likes to make a class more difficult than it really is. Her exams and midterms are fair and not so bad. But she tells you what she expects for a paper and you do it, then she screws you over and grades you badly. Prof Hogan if you're reading this, why you do dis to me?

Course only has 1 midterm, a final, and a lab component. The midterm was fair, the lab portion is a good grade booster, but the final was a mind game. Questions are poorly worded, and exam questions have mistakes. Hogan is a pretty poor prof, and makes it clear she doesn't want to be there. Condescending, rude, and belittles students. Study hard.

Not the worst prof I've ever had but not the greatest either. She is undoubtedly a caring and knowledgeable lady (with some interesting and often funny stories/anecdotes). However, she tends to be condescending and unapproachable as well. Her midterm was fair, but the final was tricky and contained concepts that were not widely covered in class.

midterm was alright, final was ridiculous, no words to describe it. No matter how much you study for it, you will not do well. questions poorly phrased, many times had nothing to do with what we learned and focused on obscure details. Prof was nice to the class, had stories but was very scary and I would not approach. Makes students feel stupid.
easy to pass if you come to class every time. She is disorganized, but she makes it easy to get good mark.

Really engaging speaker. Midterms were a joke, so easy. Project was kind of unguided, but got a great grade with minimal effort. Easiest A I ever got in HSS. Just make sure to go to class, she gives loads of hints on exam material.

Her assignments and midterms are fair, and her lectures are stimulating even when discussing difficult or dull subject matter. If you participate she'll give you lot's of extra information and answers, and she gets to know a lot of her students well.

Worst professor I've ever had. Usually If I don't like a prof I understand that his/her teaching style does not match my learning style. But this prof is by far the worst at the university. She's rude, is no help, does not answer emails, makes fun of her students, and singles people out who question her. Do not take her class.

I really wanted to like her, exams were fair, plenty of time for assignments and tonnes of examples in class on key concepts -- only drawback is that she's intimidating and not very approachable when it comes to asking questions.

KA was the least helpful/worst prof I've ever had in my 4yrs. She didn't respond to emails, had no compassion for her students if they expressed they were struggling, and thought her comms class were "just arts students who party" (her exact words). She refused to clarify slides or concepts. If you have to take this class, DO NOT take it with her.

Attendance doesn't count for anything, but she gives so many answers in her powerpoints to exams but doesn't post the same ones on BB! She does ramble, but was very helpful for tricky content. No textbook, just online readings or PDF. Beware group projects!

If you can avoid her, do so. She is the most condescending prof I have ever encountered. Not pleasant to talk to, and is just rambles on about herself and her life for most of the lectures.  She also grades really harshly for someone who provides zero guidance. AVOID.

Great prof! I agree she likes to talk about herself, but who wouldn't, she's got great stories! I regret buying the textbook, I maybe opened it once. The assignment wasn't that bad, she just didn't give any instructions on it. Did it the night before and got an 80, whereas some people did it weeks in advance and got a 60! Her midterms are so easy!

Kerry-Anne seems nice at first, but BEWARE. She is very condescending and loves to talk about herself and her PhD. The paper is brutally graded - my partner and I got a 65 and that was a high grade (average was 55) - and she gives zero guidance regarding what she wants for it.  However, exams are easy! Study and you can get a good grade.

She spends most of the class talking about herself and then rushes through slides at the end. Not approachable at all and is very rude when you try to ask her a question. Her exam questions are written poorly.

I personally found her condescending and aggressive. When asking for clarification, I received no clear answers. She also talks about how awesome she thinks she is a lot. Don't mention if you want to be a doctor, she doesn't respect that decision.

The key to success in her class is to teach yourself the course via textbook. She's a nice enough prof and definitely cares about her students. She holds comprehensive review sessions before exams which are helpful. She's great to students she likes, so get on get good side.

The textbook was a better resource than KA and that's saying a lot. She was not able to effectively convey the course material, nor was she able to answer questions posed by the class. Not to mention she has a ridiculous God complex and is a condescending passive agressive individual in general. AVOID. The good side is she gives many hints to exams

-No syllabus for the first class, but expected us to have readings complete -Midterm grades were marked incorrectly due to scantron mistakes -Labs were posted too late to prepare for, and were on material we had not learned yet (But overall, an easy 20%) -Added questions to the final exam that she had not taught/stated wouldn't be testable

I've seen condescending mentioned before but I gotta repeat it! While the 20 mark for the lab are almost grantee, the midterm out of 30 is pretty decent. For the final I guess she decided we want see her again and ask her questions about how a certain question is related to anything in the course, she decided to play free! (avoid her)

I'm gunna keep this review as objective as possible. Although she can be condescending, KerryAnn cares about her students. The midterm and labs were easy, but the final was ridiculously, disproportionally hard. I studied the same as I did for the midterm, went into the final with 95% and I'm pretty sure I left with an 8. Take another prof.

Good lecturer, tries to make it bearable for a 7pm-10pm. I usually would skip a night class, but she made it worth it to go imo. Slides are clear. She offers exam hints during class. She claimed the assignment was "similar to Master's", and we had no guidance from her. Exam grades were in the 80s, project grades were around 55.

It's a pretty basic course if you pay attention and read the textbook, but don't expect to learn anything from her. She is confusing, and super patronizing to students. And has a SERIOUS issue with cell phones. She tries to convince you every class how great everyone thinks she is, which she isn't. I taught myself.

Given it was her first time teaching this stats class she did a pretty good job. The material is hard no matter who is teaching it but she does a decent job of breaking it down. Read the chapters for examples and more detailed explanations. Most of the time her slides are cut down and she gives lots of details and examples in class.

Is the least approchable teacher with a condescending and snobby attitude! Worst teaching abilities. she talks and spends a great amount of time speaking about herself, youtube videos, and her personal life with no relation to the course. Then rushes through slides.  AVOID! and most importantly very rude

Dr Hogan is a great professor. She has clear expectations, she tells you exactly what to study for and that is what is on her tests. The course is not a bird course, but go to class, participate (the more the class participates the more hints she gives), do your readings and you will do well.

She isn't the nicest. Attend her lectures, the textbook is useless. The midterms don't relate too much to the slides, in depth. It's mainly 80% easy questions and 20% are meant to trick you to lower the class average. Read her questions carefully as there are often tricks in them. Will help you, but you need to email her and see her outside of clas

Misunderstood. She likes her students and is very passionate about what she teaches, but she makes things way too complicated, and you need to really tolerate her all through the semester. Not the best option for a profclass.

My experience with her was awful. I found her lectures to be a incredible waste of my time. She did include occasional hints in lectures about the content of the midterms however every lecture was plagued by useless time consuming and irrelevant YouTube videos. I found her to be rude and inconsiderate.

Take Det of Health with her if you can, do yourself a huge favour! An easy AA+ for sure, she gives helpful hints on her slides if you go to lectures, sends out mini study guides for the quizzes etc. Likes to interacts with students and have class discussions, besides she is an RN herself and tells many relevant "real life" stories.

Never skip a class, she puts hints in her slides for quizzesmidterms! She doesn't put up with any nonsense, be mature and pay attention to her lecture. She will call you out on talking during lectures. One girl rolled her eyes at her and Kerry-Ann put her in her place. HSS1101 is a breeze to ace the course if you show up and do the readings.

She is really awesome and committed to making the class as great a resource as possible for all the future nursing students she teaches. You ABSOLUTELY want her for Determinants of Health. All other profs were unspecialized and boring. She was funny, sweet and taught lasting information. Thank you KA!
She tells you what is going to be tested and is clear with her expectation. It is not a hard class, but if you want to know what is on the quizzes, go to class. She's amazing!

She doesn't use the textbook, at all. If you use the textbook to study, you will legitimately get a worse mark than if you study her slides. Unclear on what will be on midterms, but final exam was very easy. Wouldn't recommend.

Very rude; says she's fair & sends out emails that she will be deleting all emails regarding last midterm. Thinks she's a god. Approach her with a question she'll treat you like garbage. Said once in class that poor people do not appreciate education and how people from the Bahamas are crazy and lack of laws.. Does not even know what's in the book

Two words...God complex. This is probably the worst professor I have ever had. Every time the class doesn't understand a concept, she skips it and threatens to put it on the test. One girl was not done writing the assignment question and asked to go back a slide and Hogan just said "No" and kept going. Very condescending and moody.
EXTREMELY condescending. States she is fair but is incredibly rude. I would avoid.

The prof is very fair. Her assignments/midterm reflected what was taught. No trick questions. She is nice and tried to engage people in discussion by giving out candy. One thing I don't like is that if she asks a question and no one knows the answer, she doesn't address it and just moves on!

There is no one more condensing than Hogan; very difficult to talk to. Found her lectures extremely painful to sit through as she expects students to participate at all times, and when we don't she skips over the information she was asking us about as some sort of punishment. Gives us incomplete slides, doesn't even know what's in the textbook..

She is amazing, my favourite prof so far. Her teaching is so refreshing! She encourages participation (by giving out candy), her midterms are fair and she is very open to helping students. A little intimidating at first, but you soon get to learn about her experience as a nurse and researcher. She really know her stuff! Highly recommended!!

Hogan's descriptive, encourages questions, and is pretty clear in terms of what she's looking for regarding midterms. She has a bit of a superiority complex but is willing to help you out if you ask. She actively attempts to learn names and recognizes faces. Go to her class, ask questions and study. Not a hard course if you prepare. Go for candy!
awsome prof, but suggestible to read the notes, attend her class and pray she would not give a cross word for test
3 weeks in and she is soooooo cool!!1
awesome prof
Awesome prof.  Works really hard to make learning fun and her class is worth going to
Best professor of my undergrad! made learning and lectures enjoyable. Thanks KA!
Not Ugh. Good teaching. Has changed drastically for the better! Thanks KA!
best teacher i've ever had.
Works hard to make learning fun!
UGH.
Incredibly rude.
